Peace, cousin, say no more! And now I will unclasp a secret book, And to your quick-conceiving discontents I’ll read you matter deep and dangerous, As full of peril and adventurous spirit As to o'er-walk a curljent roaring loud On the unsteadfast footing of a spear.
